Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding the Barbell with both hands in front just past shoulder width.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at the hips with a slight bend in your knees, keeping your back straight.
Instruction.3: Engage your shoulder blades, as if you are trying to touch them together.
Instruction.4: Release the shrug.

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet about hip-width apart, with a barbell in front of you.
Instruction.2: Bend down and grab the barbell with an overhand grip, your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Keep your back straight and your shoulders down as you grip the bar.
Instruction.3: Stand up straight, lifting the barbell off the ground and pulling it toward your hips. Keep your elbows close to your body and your shoulders down as you do this.
Instruction.4: Once the barbell is at your hips, raise your shoulders as high as you can, holding the position for a moment.

Instruction.1: Take a double overhand roughly shoulder width grip.
Instruction.2: Pull your elbows straight up the ceiling. Aim to get the bar to chin level or slightly higher.

Instruction.1: Begin by sitting on the ground with your legs extended and a barbell in your hands, with your palms facing forward and your elbows bent.
Instruction.2: Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, lift the barbell up from your chest and press it straight up above your head.
Instruction.3: Lower the barbell back down to your chest.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, grip the barbell slightly wider than shoulder-width, and keep your back straight.
Instruction.2: Drive through your legs, extending your hips, knees, and ankles explosively while pulling the barbell upward.
Instruction.3: As the bar rises, pull it close to your body, leading with your elbows until it reaches chest level.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, gripping the barbell with a wide (snatch-width) grip. Keep your back straight, chest up, and bar close to your body.
Instruction.2: Drive through your legs, extending your hips, knees, and ankles while pulling the barbell up explosively.
Instruction.3: Shrug your shoulders forcefully and pull the bar as high as possible, keeping elbows above the bar.
Instruction.4: Lower the bar back to the starting position in a controlled manner and reset for the next rep.

Instruction.1: Grab a barbell with a shoulder width pronated or supinated grip.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at your hips while maintaining a flat back.
Instruction.3: Pull the weight toward your upper abdomen.
Instruction.4: Lower the weight in a controlled manner and repeat.

Instruction.1: Position a barbell in a landmine or corner of a room and stand facing it with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Grasp the end of the barbell with an overhand grip, keeping your arms straight and your shoulders relaxed.
Instruction.3: Bend at the hips and knees to lower your torso until it is almost parallel to the ground.
Instruction.4: Pull the barbell towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together as you row the weight up.

Instruction.1: Position a barbell in a landmine or corner of a room and stand facing sideways with a staggered stance and your feet shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Grasp the end of the barbell with an overhand grip, keeping your arms straight and your shoulders relaxed.
Instruction.3: Bend at the hips and knees to lower your torso until it is almost parallel to the ground.
Instruction.4: Pull the barbell towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together as you row the weight up.

Instruction.1: Start hinged forward with a flat back and the plates resting on the floor. Make sure your elbows are fully extended.
Instruction.2: Pull the bar to your sternum.
Instruction.3: Return the plates back to the floor and let the bar come to a full dead stop.
Instruction.4: Then initiate the next rep.

Instruction.1: Grab the barbell with an overhand grip. Hinge forward while keeping your back flat until your torso is about parallel with the ground.
Instruction.2: Let your arms hang freely.
Instruction.3: Pull the bar to your torso while tucking your elbows in slightly.
Instruction.4: Extend your elbows fully before initiating the next rep.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing in front of a barbell with your feet about hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Bend at the hips and knees to grab the barbell with a supinated (underhand) grip, positioning the barbell about an inch away from your shins.
Instruction.3: Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, use your back muscles to lift the barbell straight up towards your chest.
Instruction.4: As the barbell reaches your chest, pause briefly, and then lower the barbell back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Position a barbell in a landmine or corner of a room and stand facing it with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Grasp the end of the barbell with a neutral grip, keeping your arms straight and your shoulders relaxed.
Instruction.3: Bend at the hips and knees to lower your torso until it is almost parallel to the ground.
Instruction.4: Pull the barbell towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together as you row the weight up.

Instruction.1: Grab a v bar and place it under the bar's collar.
Instruction.2: Hinge forward with a flat back and pull your elbows straight back toward the ceiling.
Instruction.3: Fully extend your elbows before initiating the next rep.

Instruction.1: Place the bar on your traps. You may need a pad so the bar doesn't dig into your cervical spine.
Instruction.2: Push your hips straight back. Your knees should stay MOSTLY extended (think soft knees). Also make sure to
Instruction.3: Look for what feels like a stretch in your hamstrings. The stretch feeling means you're likely nearing the end of your Range of Motion without rounding your spine.
Instruction.4: When you feel the stretch push your hips forward until you're in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Place the bar between your traps and rear delts. Pull your shoulder blades back to give the bar a shelf to sit on.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings. This means you're nearing the end of your Range of Motion with out rounding your spine.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch push your hips forward until you'e in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Stance width can vary with a sumo DL. Some prefer toes near the plates. Others prefer a more narrow stance to get more drive off the floor.
Instruction.2: Make sure your arms are inside your legs. The bar should be just over your mid-foot. Flatten your back and push your heels into the floor.
Instruction.3: Try to extend your knees and hips simultaneously.

Instruction.1: Take a shoulder width, double overhand or mixed grip.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back while leaving your knees mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet hip-width apart and place a barbell on the floor in front of you.
Instruction.2: Bend at the hips and knees to grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, positioning your hands just outside of your hips.
Instruction.3: Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, lift the barbell off the floor by extending your hips and knees.
Instruction.4: As you lift the barbell, pull your shoulders back and squeeze your glutes to fully extend your hips at the top of the movement.

Instruction.1: Stand in front of a box or bench with your feet shoulder-width apart and a barbell resting on your upper back.
Instruction.2: Lower your body into a squat position, sitting back onto the box and pausing for a moment before standing back up.
Instruction.3: Push through your heels to return to the standing position.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and a barbell resting on your upper back.
Instruction.2: Lower your body into a squat position, pausing for a moment at the bottom of the movement before standing back up.
Instruction.3: Push through your heels to return to the standing position.

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet about hip-width apart, with your toes pointed slightly outward.
Instruction.2: Place a barbell on the floor behind you, with the weight plates on either side.
Instruction.3: Bend down and grab the barbell with an overhand grip, your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Keep your back straight and your shoulders down as you grip the bar.
Instruction.4: Stand up straight, lifting the barbell off the ground and pulling it toward your hips. Keep your elbows close to your body and your shoulders down as you do this.

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet about hip-width apart, with your toes pointed slightly outward.
Instruction.2: Place a barbell on the floor in front of you, with the weight plates on either side. Make sure that the bar is directly in line with your feet.
Instruction.3: Bend down and grab the barbell with an overhand grip, your hands much wider than shoulder-width apart. Keep your back straight and your shoulders down as you grip the bar.
Instruction.4: Stand up straight, lifting the barbell off the ground and pulling it toward your hips. Keep your elbows close to your body and your shoulders down as you do this.
Instruction.5: Slowly lower the barbell back to the ground, making sure to keep your back straight and your shoulders down throughout the movement.

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet about hip-width apart. The bar should be in a rack or box so it's lifted off the ground.
Instruction.2: Grab the barbell with an overhand grip, your hands should be much wider than shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.3: Hing forward at the hips keeping your knees mostly extended. Hinge until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.4: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you are back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing with your feet hip-width apart and holding a barbell at one side of your body, with your palms facing your thighs.
Instruction.2: Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, bend at the hips and knees to lower the barbell down towards the ground.
Instruction.3: As the barbell reaches the ground, use your legs and glutes to push through your heels and extend your hips and knees to raise your body back to the starting position.
Instruction.4: Repeat the movement for the desired number of reps, then switch sides and repeat the exercise with the barbell on the opposite side of your body.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing with your feet about hip-width apart and holding a barbell in the crook of your elbows, with your palms facing towards your body.
Instruction.2: Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, bend at the hips and lower your torso forward until it is nearly parallel to the ground.
Instruction.3: Push through your heels to extend your hips and raise your body back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing with your feet about hip-width apart and holding a barbell in the crook of your arms, near your belly. Your palms should be facing towards your body.
Instruction.2: Sit back and lower your body down until your thighs are parallel to the ground, keeping your back straight and your core engaged.
Instruction.3: Push through your heels to extend your hips and stand back up to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand in front of the landmine with your feet hip-width apart and your knees slightly bent. Grasp the landmine barbell with both hands, palms facing each other, and hold it in front of your thighs.
Instruction.2: Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, hinge at the hips and push your hips back, allowing the landmine to travel down your thighs. Lower the landmine by bending forward at the hips while keeping your back flat, allowing the barbell to move closer to the floor. Continue the movement until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings, keeping your legs relatively straight but with a slight bend in the knees.
Instruction.3: Reverse the movement by pushing your hips forward and driving through your heels while keeping your back straight.
Instruction.4: Repeat for the desired number of reps.

Instruction.1: Hold the end of the bar in front of you.
Instruction.2: Pop your hips, pull your elbows up to the ceiling, and get underneath the bar.

Instruction.1: Pull your shoulder blades back really hard and place the bar on your posterior delts.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back and break at the knees to initiate the squat.
Instruction.3: Aim to get your hamstrings to parallel with the ground. Push your heels into the floor and squat back up to a standing position.

Instruction.1: Grab the end of the landmine and stand perpendicular to the bar.
Instruction.2: Lift your inside leg and keep your outside leg planted.
Instruction.3: Push your hips back keeping your knees mostly extended. When you feel the stretch in your hams, push your hips forward until you are standing upright.

Instruction.1: Stand in a staggered position. With the back leg bent and the front mostly extended.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back until you feel a stretch through your front hamstring.
Instruction.3: Push your hips back forward until you are standing.

Instruction.1: Stand with your mid-foot under the bar, plates should be on blocks, and grip the bar with your hands, about a shoulder width apart.
Instruction.2: Bend your knees, then lift the bar by straightening your back. It is important to keep your back straight.
Instruction.3: Stand to your full height and hold.
Instruction.4: Lower the bar to the floor by bending your knees and keeping your back straight.

Instruction.1: Set up for a standard deadlift, grip the barbell.
Instruction.2: Lift, pause at knee height.
Instruction.3: Hold briefly, then complete the lift; reset and repeat for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Stand with your mid-foot under the bar, feet should be on a plate or elevated platform, and grip the bar with your hands, about a shoulder width apart.
Instruction.2: Bend your knees, then lift the bar by straightening your back. It is important to keep your back straight.
Instruction.3: Stand to your full height and hold.
Instruction.4: Lower the bar to the floor by bending your knees and keeping your back straight.

Instruction.1: Stand centered over the barbell, feet shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Grip the bar with both hands, one in front, one behind.
Instruction.3: Lift by driving through your heels, keeping your back straight, then lower slowly.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing with your feet hip-width apart with the bar on the ground at your side.
Instruction.2: Lift the bar to your side and walk for the allotted amount of time or distance.
Instruction.3: Set the bar down and switch sides.

Instruction.1: Set up for a sumo deadlift, grip the barbell.
Instruction.2: Lift, pause at knee height.
Instruction.3: Hold briefly, then complete the lift; reset and repeat for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, grip the bar just outside your knees. Pull the bar from the floor by driving through your legs, keeping your back straight.
Instruction.2: As the bar reaches your hips, extend explosively, shrug, and drop under to catch it in a front squat position with elbows high. Stand up tall.
Instruction.3: Dip slightly, then drive through your legs to push the bar overhead.
Instruction.4: Stabilize the bar overhead, lock arms, then bring feet together before lowering the bar safely.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, grip the barbell with a wide overhand grip, and keep your back straight and core engaged.
Instruction.2: Lift the barbell by explosively extending your hips, knees, and ankles while keeping the bar close to your body.
Instruction.3: As the bar reaches chest level, rotate your wrists and elbows up and back, transitioning into an overhead press.
Instruction.4: Fully extend your arms overhead, stabilize the bar, then lower it back to the starting position with control.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, barbell over midfoot. Grip the bar wide (outside shoulders), hook grip recommended.
Instruction.2: Keep chest up, back straight, and drive through heels to lift the bar off the ground, keeping it close to your body.
Instruction.3: As the bar reaches mid-thigh, explode upwards by extending hips, knees, and ankles, shrugging shoulders and pulling the bar high.
Instruction.4: Drop under the bar slightly, catching it overhead with arms locked out. Stand up fully to complete the lift.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, barbell over midfoot. Grip the bar wide with an overhand grip, chest up, and back straight.
Instruction.2: Lift the bar by driving through your legs, keeping it close to your body. Extend your hips and knees while maintaining a straight back.
Instruction.3: Explosively extend your hips, knees, and ankles while shrugging your shoulders. Pull yourself under the bar as it moves upward.
Instruction.4: Drop into a deep squat while locking the bar overhead. Stabilize, then stand up fully to complete the lift.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing with your feet on a plate and holding a barbell in the crook of your arms, near your belly. Your palms should be facing towards your body.
Instruction.2: Step back with one foot off the plate and lower your back knee to the floor.
Instruction.3: Push through your front leg and bring your back foot to the plate.

Instruction.1: Place the bar on a lower rung so that when gripped your arms are fully extended and your back is straight.
Instruction.2: Grip at shoulder width, raise the bar with your shoulders and pause at the contracted position.
Instruction.3: Slowly lower the bar back to starting position.

Instruction.1: Have a seat on the machine, and grab each handle.
Instruction.2: Pull your shoulder blades straight up toward the ceiling.

Instruction.1: Grab both handles and stand upright. Make sure you keep a flat back while lifting to the starting position.
Instruction.2: Pull your shoulder blades straight up toward the ceiling.

Instruction.1: Grip the bar with the palms facing forward, your hands need to be spaced out at a distance wider than shoulder width.
Instruction.2: As you have both arms extended in front of you holding the bar, bring your torso back around 30 degrees while sticking your chest out.
Instruction.3: Pull the bar down to about chin level or a little lower in a smooth movement whilst squeezing the shoulder blades together.
Instruction.4: After a second of squeezing, slowly raise the bar back to the starting position when your arms are fully extended.

Instruction.1: Sit with your back straight on the machine and grip the handles.
Instruction.2: Pull the handles back using your arms. Your legs and torso should be at a 90° angle. Push out your chest.
Instruction.3: Pull the handles towards your body until your hands are beside your abdomen.

Instruction.1: Use the Straight Bar attachment. Hold with an underhand grip.
Instruction.2: Hold the attachment as you sit on the machine and put your legs under the leg pads.
Instruction.3: Pull the bar to your clavicle, then raise back up until your arm are extended.

Instruction.1: Use the Straight Bar attachment.
Instruction.2: Hold the attachment as you sit on the machine and put your legs under the leg pads.
Instruction.3: Pull the bar to your clavicle, then raise back up until your arm are extended.

Instruction.1: Use the V Bar attachment.
Instruction.2: Hold the attachment as you sit on the machine and put your legs under the leg pads.
Instruction.3: Pull the bar to your clavicle, then raise back up until your arm are extended.

Instruction.1: Adjust weight for assistance. Stand on platform, grip handles above shoulder-width. Knees on pad if available.
Instruction.2: Slowly pull up until chin is above the bar. Keep elbows close, core engaged.
Instruction.3: Lower back with control. Pause at bottom. Repeat for reps.

Instruction.1: Adjust weight for assistance. Stand on platform, grip handles above shoulder-width. Knees on pad if available.
Instruction.2: Slowly pull up until chin is above the bar. Keep elbows close, core engaged.
Instruction.3: Lower back with control. Pause at bottom. Repeat for reps.

Instruction.1: Adjust weight for assistance. Stand on platform, grip handles above shoulder-width. Knees on pad if available.
Instruction.2: Slowly pull up until chin is above the bar. Keep elbows close, core engaged.
Instruction.3: Lower back with control. Pause at bottom. Repeat for reps.

Instruction.1: Adjust weight for assistance. Stand on platform, grip handles above shoulder-width. Knees on pad if available.
Instruction.2: Slowly pull up until chin is above the bar. Keep elbows close, core engaged.
Instruction.3: Lower back with control. Pause at bottom. Repeat for reps.

Instruction.1: Sit on the machine, feet flat, and grab the handles with palms facing up, keeping your back straight.
Instruction.2: Pull handles towards your lower abdomen, squeezing your shoulder blades together. Keep elbows close to your body.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to the starting position, fully extending your arms without locking elbows. Repeat for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Sit on the machine, feet flat, and grab the handles with palms facing each other, keeping your back straight.
Instruction.2: Pull handles towards your lower abdomen, squeezing your shoulder blades together. Keep elbows close to your body.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to the starting position, fully extending your arms without locking elbows. Repeat for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Place your foot on the leg pad for leverage and grab the attachment.
Instruction.2: Start with your arms extended and your head between your arms.
Instruction.3: Begin to pull. As you pull, lean backwards until the attachment touches your chest.

WorkoutName: Machine Chest Supported T Bar Row

Instruction.1: Lay on the chest pad and grab the handles. Lift the bar out of the holding hook.
Instruction.2: Pull the bar to your chest and then fully extend your elbows at the bottom of each rep.

Instruction.1: Grip the handles with the palms facing down.
Instruction.2: Sit on the machine and press your knees into the knee pad.
Instruction.3: Pull the handles until your upper arm is even with your torso, or just behind your torso.
Instruction.4: Extend until your elbows are fully extended before initiating the next rep.

Instruction.1: Sit on the machine, feet flat, and grab the handles.
Instruction.2: Pull handles towards your lower abdomen, squeezing your shoulder blades together. Keep elbows close to your body.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to the starting position, fully extending your arms without locking elbows. Repeat for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Lay on the chest after adjusting the height off the bar holding hooks to match your arm length.
Instruction.2: Remove the bar from the hooks, then initiate the set.
Instruction.3: Pull the bar straight back, then lower to the start position. Fully extend your elbows at the bottom of each rep.
Instruction.4: Lay on the chest after adjusting the height off the bar holding hooks to match your arm length.
Instruction.5: Remove the bar from the hooks, then initiate the set.
Instruction.6: Pull the bar straight back, then lower to the start position. Fully extend your elbows at the bottom of each rep.

WorkoutName: Machine Plate Loaded T Bar Row

Instruction.1: Hinge forward while keeping your back flat.
Instruction.2: Grab the handles and pull the weight toward your chest.
Instruction.3: Make sure to fully extend your elbows at the bottom of each rep. Also make sure to not use momentum.

Instruction.1: Adjust the seating pad for your height.
Instruction.2: Place your elbows on the elbow pad. Pull the bar forward until it nearly touches your stomach.

Instruction.1: Position your thighs on the padding and hook your feet on the platform supports.
Instruction.2: Keeping your back straight, slowly bend at your waist until your legs and back are at a 45° angle.
Instruction.3: Slowly raise your body to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Sit on the machine and place your upper back on the rolling pad.
Instruction.2: Extend your hips and lower back. Make sure not to hyperextend your spine.

Instruction.1: Lay on the pad and grab the handles.
Instruction.2: Slip your legs into the belt loop.
Instruction.3: Push your legs back until they are horizontal with the ground.
Instruction.4: Lower back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Press your chest into the chest pad and grab the horizontal handles with an overhand grip.
Instruction.2: Pull the handles toward you, make sure your elbows stay flared out.

Instruction.1: Stand upright with your feet shoulder width apart.
Instruction.2: Nod your head forward, bringing your chin to your chest.
Instruction.3: You will feel the stretch across your neck.

Instruction.1: Stand upright with your feet shoulder width apart.
Instruction.2: Keeping your chest facing forward, turn your head 90 degrees to the left. Then return to centre point.
Instruction.3: Repeat, turning your head in the other direction.

Instruction.1: Stand upright with your feet shoulder width apart.
Instruction.2: Place your left hand on your head and gently pull your head down towards your left shoulder. Then return to centre point.
Instruction.3: Repeat, using your right hand pulling towards your right shoulder.

Instruction.1: Find a wall to lean against, lay your tricep against the wall with your hand behind your back.
Instruction.2: Slowly lean into the wall.
Instruction.3: Return to starting position, then switch sides.

Instruction.1: Stand up right and raise your hand to a full stretch above your head.
Instruction.2: Slowly lean across your body and trace the opposite hand down your leg.
Instruction.3: Hold at the bottom of the stretch, return to starting position and then switch sides.

Instruction.1: Place both hands on the wall in front of you.
Instruction.2: Slowly lower your body until you feel the stretch.
Instruction.3: Hold at the bottom of the stretch, return to starting position.

Instruction.1: Lay flat against the ground with your knees at an angle and your feet flat against the floor.
Instruction.2: Grab your legs just below the knees, and pull your legs towards your chest.
Instruction.3: Pause at the apex of the stretch, then return to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Lay on your back with your arms at either side.
Instruction.2: Raise your knees so that they are pointing straight towards the ceiling. Keeping your legs pressed together, rotate your hips to either side.
Instruction.3: Repeat this motion as necessary.

Instruction.1: Lay flat on the floor with your arms at either side.
Instruction.2: With one leg, hook one foot under the joint of your other leg.
Instruction.3: Rotate your hips so that your knees are pointing sideways, keeping your hooked leg flat against the floor.
Instruction.4: Pause at the apex of the stretch and repeat with your other leg.

Instruction.1: Sit on the floor with the tops of your feet pointed and flat on the ground. Move your arms out in front of you in the diving position, placing your palms flat against the ground.
Instruction.2: With your arms fully extended, rest your buttocks on the heels of your feet, you can crawl your hands forward to extend the stretch if need be.
Instruction.3: Hold the extended position for a few seconds, and return to starting position.

WorkoutName: Traps mid back Stretch Variation Two

Instruction.1: Sit on the ground and lay one leg flat and the other over the top.
Instruction.2: Hold your leg with the same side arm and slowly rotate your hips and back.
Instruction.3: Hold at the peak of the stretch, then slowly return to starting position.
Instruction.4: Switch sides and repeat.

WorkoutName: Traps mid back Stretch Variation One

Instruction.1: Stand up with your feet shoulder width apart. Place one arm across the front of your chest at shoulder height, press the forearm of your other arm above the elbow, hooking the stretching arm with your hand.
Instruction.2: Press the arm until it is straight and rotate your upper torso to engage the stretch even deeper.
Instruction.3: Repeat with your other arm.

Instruction.1: Start by standing upright with your feet shoulder-width apart. Hold a single weight plate overhead with both hands, keeping your arms extended straight above your head.
Instruction.2: Begin walking forward, taking slow and steady steps while maintaining a straight line. Your focus should be on maintaining balance and control of the weight plate overhead.
Instruction.3: As you walk, continue to keep your arms extended and the weight plate overhead. Try to maintain good posture and avoid leaning forward or backward, as this could result in losing control of the weight plate.
Instruction.4: Continue walking for a set distance or for a certain amount of time, keeping your focus on proper form and technique. When finished, return to the starting position and repeat as desired.

Instruction.1: Stand tall with a weight plate overhead.
Instruction.2: Elevated and depress your scapula.
Instruction.3: Avoid leaning forward or backwards to keep pressure off of your lumbar spine.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder width apart. Hold each plate to the side of you.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at the hips bringing the plates to the floor while you slightly bend your knees, keeping your back straight.
Instruction.3: One at a time, lift the plate up. Return the plate to the floor and do the other side.

Instruction.1: Lay flat on the ground with a plate on your chest.
Instruction.2: Push your hips up toward the ceiling and maintain that extended position.
Instruction.3: Extend your elbows mostly, break at the shoulder joint while maintaining hip extension and the slight bend in your elbows.
Instruction.4: Let the plate tap the floor (or get close) and then pull the plate back into the starting position.

Instruction.1: Make sure to keep your elbow close to your body and your core engaged throughout the movement.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at your hips while maintaining a flat back.
Instruction.3: Pull the plate toward your upper abdomen.
Instruction.4: Lower the weight in a controlled manner and repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand facing the plate with your feet shoulder-width apart and the plate positioned between your feet.
Instruction.2: Bend down and grasp the plate from the top edges with both hands, making sure your thumbs and fingers are evenly spaced.
Instruction.3: Keep your back straight, chest up and core engaged, and stand up with the plate, keeping it close to your body.
Instruction.4: Lower the plate back down to the ground, keeping control and maintaining good posture.

Instruction.1: Lay underneath a fixed horizontal bar and grab the bar with a wide overhand grip. Place a plate on your chest.
Instruction.2: Pull your body straight up to the bar.
Instruction.3: Return to the starting position, your arms fully extended. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Grab the bar shoulder width apart with a supinated grip (palms facing you). Use a dip belt and the let the weight hang between your legs.
Instruction.2: With your body hanging and arms fully extended, pull yourself up until your chin is past the bar.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to starting position. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, arms and shoulders fully extended. Weight hanging between your legs.
Instruction.2: Pull your body up until your chin is above the bar.
Instruction.3: Lower your body back to starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, the plate in front of the feet, and the knees slightly bent.
Instruction.2: Bend the hips and knees to grip the plate with palms facing the body.
Instruction.3: Keeping the back straight, stand up while lifting the plate off the ground.
Instruction.4: Return the plate back to the starting position by bending the hips and knees, keeping control of the plate.

WorkoutName: Plate Single Leg Pinch Grip Deadlift

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and facing forwards. Grip the sides of a weight plate with your palms facing down.
Instruction.2: Balance on one foot, as you raise the weight keep your arms and back straight, while you bring your  other foot back towards the ground
Instruction.3: Keep four raised leg straight and in alignment with your back as you lower the plate back down to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, the plate held in front of you, and the knees slightly bent.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at the hips, keeping the back straight, until the torso is parallel to the floor.
Instruction.3: Push through the hips to return to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, the plate held behind the neck and the knees slightly bent.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at the hips, keeping the back straight, until the torso is parallel to the floor.
Instruction.3: Push through the hips to return to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Engage your core and straighten your legs to lift the plate off the ground.
Instruction.2: Stand on one leg, keeping the other leg off the ground, while holding the plate in front of your body.
Instruction.3: Keep your back straight and maintain a neutral head position while looking straight ahead.
Instruction.4: Lower the plate back down to the ground while keeping your balance on one leg.

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a weight plate.
Instruction.2: Place one foot slightly behind the other, with the heel of your back foot elevated.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, bend at the hips and knees to lower the plate towards the ground, keeping your back straight and your core engaged.
Instruction.4: Once the plate is below your knees, drive through your heels to stand back up to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding two plates with a pinch grip.
Instruction.2: Place one foot slightly behind the other, with the heel of your back foot elevated.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, bend at the hips and knees to lower the plates towards the ground, keeping your back straight and your core engaged.

Instruction.1: Hold a plate in both hands.
Instruction.2: Pull your arms and legs off the ground while and hold that position.

Instruction.1: Lay flat on the ground on your stomach with your arms extended overhead. Hold a plate with a neutral grip.
Instruction.2: Lift your legs and chest off the ground simultaneously and hold for a 1 count at the top.
Instruction.3: Relax your lower back and lower your legs and chest back to the floor.

Instruction.1: Set up a bar at mid way up your quad. Place the working leg against the bar.
Instruction.2: Place one foot behind. You should only be on your toes on that back foot. Your front foot should be planted flat the entire time.
Instruction.3: Bend your back knee and push your hips back. Look for a stretch in your front hamstring.
Instruction.4: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward again until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Place a barbell at about midway up your thigh. Press your quads into the barbell. Hold a plate up to your chest.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back while leaving your knees mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you're back in a standing position.

WorkoutName: Plate Internally Rotated Rear Delt Fly

Instruction.1: With plates in either hand, bend your knees with your feet slightly bowed out. Hinge forward with a flat back.
Instruction.2: Maintain an overhand grip and internally rotated shoulders.
Instruction.3: Raise your arms backward toward the ceiling while maintaining a light band in your elbows.

Instruction.1: Keep your back straight and bend forward slightly at the waist.
Instruction.2: With arms extended, raise the weights out to your sides until they are in line with your shoulders.
Instruction.3: Pause briefly and then lower the weights back to the starting position.

WorkoutName: Bosu Ball Single Leg Hip Thrust

Instruction.1: Take a double overhand roughly shoulder width grip.
Instruction.2: Pull your elbows straight up the ceiling. Aim to get the bar to chin level or slightly higher.
Instruction.3: lower the bar and repeat.

Instruction.1: Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, arms and shoulders fully extended. Leave your feet on the floor.
Instruction.2: Pull your body up until your chin is above the bar. Use your legs top assist you up.
Instruction.3: Lower your body back to starting position.

Instruction.1: Lay underneath a fixed horizontal bar and grab the bar with a wide overhand grip.
Instruction.2: Pull your body straight up to the bar.
Instruction.3: Return to the starting position, your arms fully extended. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Start hinged forward with a flat back. Make sure your elbows are fully extended.
Instruction.2: Pull the bar to your sternum.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing in front of a bar with your feet about hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Bend at the hips and knees to grab the bar with a supinated (underhand) grip, positioning the bar about an inch away from your shins.
Instruction.3: Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, use your back muscles to lift the bar straight up towards your chest.
Instruction.4: As the bar reaches your chest, pause briefly, and then lower the bar back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Place one foot behind. You should only be on your toes on that back foot. Your front foot should be planted flat the entire time.
Instruction.2: Bend your back knee and push your hips back. Look for a stretch in your front hamstring.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward again until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Take a shoulder width, double overhand or mixed grip.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back while leaving your knees mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Stance width can vary with a sumo DL. Some prefer toes near the plates. Others prefer a more narrow stance to get more drive off the floor.
Instruction.2: Make sure your arms are inside your legs. The bar should be just over your mid-foot. Flatten your back and unrack the bar
Instruction.3: Leave your knees mostly extended and flex and extend your hips.

Instruction.1: Sit on a bench with dumbbells in both hands, palms facing your body, back straight.
Instruction.2: Elevate your shoulders and hold the contracted position at the apex of the motion.
Instruction.3: Slowly lower your shoulders back to starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand tall with two dumbbells. Pull your shoulder blades up. Give a one second squeeze at the top.
Lay sideways on a bench letting your arm hang freely.
Instruction.2: Pull your shoulder blade and joint toward the ceiling.

Instruction.1: Lay on an incline bench with your arms hanging freely.
Instruction.2: Pull your shoulder blades back toward the ceiling.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding dumbbells with both hands in front just past shoulder width.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at the hips with a slight bend in your knees, keeping your back straight.
Instruction.3: Engage your shoulder blades, as if you are trying to touch them together.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand with an overhand grip.
Instruction.2: Keep your back straight and chest lifted, engage your core to maintain balance.
Instruction.3: Begin the movement by lifting the dumbbell straight up towards your chin, keeping your elbow close to your body and the weight in line with your shoulder.
Instruction.4: Continue to lift the weight until it reaches the chin or neck level, keeping the elbow high and close to the body.
Instruction.5: Lower the weight back down to the starting position with control.

Instruction.1: Grab both dumbbells and hinge forward at the hips. Make sure you keep a flat back.
Instruction.2: The closer your torso is to parallel with the ground the longer the range of motion will be at your shoulder. The better the results you'll get from the exercise.
Instruction.3: Let your arms hang freely, and then pull your elbow joint straight back toward the ceiling.

Instruction.1: Brace your off arm against something stable (bench, box). Stagger your stance so your leg on the side of your working arm is back.
Instruction.2: Try to get your torso to parallel with the ground. That will extend your range of motion.
Instruction.3: Let your arm hang freely and then pull your elbow back. Imagine you've got a tennis ball in your armpit and squeeze it each rep.

Instruction.1: Grab a dumbbell and hold with both hands. Point your dumbbell at the ceiling.
Instruction.2: Flex at the shoulder joint while keeping your elbows mostly extended.
Instruction.3: Flex until you feel a stretch in your lats then bring the dumbbell back to the ceiling.

Instruction.1: The dumbbells should be set on the ground. Hinge forward while keeping a flat back.
Instruction.2: Pull one elbow back toward the ceiling and then return the dumbbell to the ground softly.
Instruction.3: Then pull with the other arm.

Instruction.1: Place one hand and one knee on a bench. Make sure you keep a flat back.
Instruction.2: Pull the dumbbell toward the ceiling.
Instruction.3: Make sure to avoid any jerking or rotating.

Instruction.1: Lay on an incline bench that is between 30-45 degrees high.
Instruction.2: Let your arms hang freely. Pull your elbows straight back toward the ceiling.

Instruction.1: The dumbbells should be placed on the floor.
Instruction.2: Hinge forward with a flat back and grab the dumbbells.
Instruction.3: Pull both dumbbells back and your elbows toward the ceiling.
Instruction.4: Return the dumbbells back to the floor softly on each rep.

Instruction.1: Start by hinging over with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Instruction.2: Bring the dumbbells to your sides, with your palms facing forward and your elbows slightly bent.
Instruction.3: Make sure to keep your core engaged and your back straight throughout the movement.

Instruction.1: Start by standing in front of a flat bench with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a dumbbell in one hand.
Instruction.2: Place your other hand on the bench for support, and bend at the waist so that your chest is parallel to the ground.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, row the dumbbell up towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blade together as you do so.
Instruction.4: Make sure to keep your elbow close to your body and your core engaged throughout the movement.

Instruction.1: Start by placing your elbow on one knee.
Instruction.2: Hold a dumbbell in your other hand, with your palm facing inwards towards your body.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, row the dumbbell up towards your chest, keeping your elbow close to your body and your core engaged.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet staggered and one hand on a bench/box. Hold a dumbbell in the opposing hand.
Instruction.2: Hinge forward at the hips, keeping the back flat,  and eyes facing forward. The weight should hang directly below the shoulders.
Instruction.3: Start with an overhand grip, as you pull rotate the dumbbell. When your upper arm reaches your side your palm should be facing forward.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet staggered and one hand on your knee. Hold a dumbbell in the opposing hand.
Instruction.2: Hinge forward at the hips, keeping the back flat, and eyes facing forward. The weight should hang directly below the shoulders.
Instruction.3: Start with an overhand grip, as you pull rotate the dumbbell. When your upper arm reaches your side your palm should be facing forward.

Instruction.1: Grab both dumbbells and hinge forward at the hips. Make sure you keep a flat back.
Instruction.2: The closer your torso is to parallel with the ground the longer the range of motion will be at your shoulder. The better the results you'll get from the exercise.
Instruction.3: Let your arms hang freely, maintain an underhand grip, and then pull your elbow joint straight back toward the ceiling.

Instruction.1: Start in a high plank position with a pair of dumbbells positioned under your shoulders. Your hands should grip the dumbbells, palms facing each other.
Instruction.2: Keep your core engaged and your back straight as you row one dumbbell up towards your hip, keeping your elbow close to your body.
Instruction.3: Lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position and repeat on the other side.

Instruction.1: Grab the bar shoulder width apart with a supinated grip (palms facing you). Use a dip belt and the let the weight hang between your legs.
Instruction.2: With your body hanging and arms fully extended, pull yourself up until your chin is past the bar.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to starting position. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, arms and shoulders fully extended.
Instruction.2: Pull your body up until your chin is above the bar.
Instruction.3: Lower your body back to starting position.

Instruction.1: Lay flat on the ground on your stomach with your arms extended overhead. Hold a dumbbell with a neutral grip.
Instruction.2: Lift your legs and chest off the ground simultaneously and hold for a 1 count at the top.
Instruction.3: Relax your lower back and lower your legs and chest back to the floor.

Instruction.1: Hold the dumbbell in a goblet position. With your elbows directly under your fists.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back while leaving your knees MOSTLY extended. You should feel a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch push your hips forward until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Stand with a shoulder width stance. Push your butt back while leaving your knees MOSTLY extended.
Instruction.2: You should feel a stretch in your hamstrings. When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward to complete the rep.
Instruction.3: Do not push your hips all the way forward. This will hyperextend your spine. Just go to a normal standing position.

Instruction.1: Place two dumbbells on your shoulders and make sure you force your elbows upward.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back and break at the knees.
Instruction.3: When you reach parallel (hamstrings parallel with the ground) pause for 1-3 seconds. Then push through your heels back to the starting position.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Single Leg Single Arm Deadlift

Instruction.1: Start by standing on one leg with a dumbbell in one hand.
Instruction.2: Slowly bend at the hips and lower the dumbbell towards the ground while extending your free leg behind you.
Instruction.3: Keep your core engaged and your back straight as you lower the weight.
Instruction.4: Once the dumbbell is close to the ground, push through your heel to return to the starting position.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Single Leg Stiff Leg Deadlift

Instruction.1: Start by standing on one leg with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding two dumbbells.
Instruction.2: From this starting position, hinge at the hips to lower the dumbbell towards the ground, keeping your back straight and your core engaged.
Instruction.3: Once you feel a stretch in your hamstring, slowly return to the starting position.
Instruction.4: Make sure to keep your standing leg slightly bent and avoid rounding your back as you lower the dumbbell.

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Instruction.2: Place one foot slightly behind the other, with the heel of your back foot elevated on a step or weight plate.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, bend at the hips and knees to lower the dumbbells towards the ground, keeping your back straight and your core engaged.
Instruction.4: Once the dumbbells are below your knees, drive through your heels to stand back up to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart and holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Instruction.2: Place the dumbbells on the ground between your feet.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, bend your knees and lower your body down into a squat.
Instruction.4: Make sure to keep your core engaged and your back straight throughout the movement.

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a dumbbell in both hands.
Instruction.2: Bend your knees slightly and hinge at the hips to swing the dumbbell between your legs.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, explosively extend your hips and swing the dumbbell up to chest height.
Instruction.4: Allow the momentum of the swing to carry the dumbbell back down between your legs, and then repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

Instruction.1: Lie face down on a mat.
Instruction.2: Hold dumbbells out in front
Instruction.3: Lift arms and legs simultaneously, squeezing lower back.

Instruction.1: Stand with a shoulder width stance holding one dumbbell. Push your butt back while leaving your knees MOSTLY extended.
Instruction.2: Reach toward the opposing leg. You should feel a stretch in your hamstrings. When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward to complete the rep.
Instruction.3: Do not push your hips all the way forward. This will hyperextend your spine. Just go to a normal standing position.

Instruction.1: Stand in front of a box or bench with your feet shoulder-width apart with a dumbbell in a goblet position.
Instruction.2: Lower your body into a squat position, sitting back onto the box and pausing for a moment before standing back up.
Instruction.3: Push through your heels to return to the standing position.

Instruction.1: Set up a bar at mid way up your quad. Place the working leg against the bar.
Instruction.2: Place one foot behind. You should only be on your toes on that back foot. Your front foot should be planted flat the entire time.
Instruction.3: Bend your back knee and push your hips back. Look for a stretch in your front hamstring.
Instruction.4: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward again until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Place a barbell at about midway up your thigh. Press your quads into the barbell.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back while leaving your knees mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you're back in a standing position.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Half Kneeling Goblet Romanian Deadlift

Instruction.1: Place one knee on a bench and hold a dumbbell in a goblet position.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back while leaving your knee mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Place one knee on a bench and hold a dumbbell.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back while leaving your knee mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Hinge forward at the hips while maintaining a flat back. Try to get your torso as close to parallel with the ground as your mobility will allow for.
Instruction.2: Let your arms hang in front of you. Pull your elbows back towards the ceiling while flaring your elbows outward.

Instruction.1: Sit on a bench. Put your chest in your lap. Try to get your torso as close to parallel with the ground as your mobility will allow for.
Instruction.2: Let your arms hang in front of you. Pull your elbows back towards the ceiling while flaring your elbows outward.

Instruction.1: Place the cable at shoulder height.
Instruction.2: On the same side as the working arm, step back and rotate outwards.
Instruction.3: Pull your elbow back while flaring your elbow out.

Instruction.1: Use a rope attachment. Cable should be set all the way to the top of the machine.
Instruction.2: Grab your attachment and walk a few steps back. Push your butt back to where you are leaning forward somewhat.
Instruction.3: Initiate the movement with your shoulders and not your elbows. Imagine trying to pull the attachment through your thighs at the bottom.

Instruction.1: Place the cable at shoulder height. Use a row bar.
Instruction.2: Pull the handles back using your arms. Push out your chest.
Instruction.3: Pull the handles towards your body until your hands are beside your abdomen.

Instruction.1: Use a handle attachment set all the way to the top of the cable crossover machine.
Instruction.2: Walk a few steps away from the cable machine. Face your body sideways.
Instruction.3: Face your palm forward. Then pull your elbow in toward your rib cage.

WorkoutName: Cable Single Arm Underhand Grip Row

Instruction.1: Place the cable at shoulder height. Use a handle attachment. Face your palm upward.
Instruction.2: Pull the handle back using your arms. Push out your chest.
Instruction.3: Pull the handle towards your body until your hands are beside your abdomen.

WorkoutName: Cable Single Arm Neutral Grip Row

Instruction.1: Use a bar attachment. Cable should be set all the way to the top of the machine.
Instruction.2: Grab your attachment and walk a few steps back. Push your butt back to where you are leaning forward somewhat.
Instruction.3: Initiate the movement with your shoulders and not your elbows. Bring one arm to your side.
Instruction.4: You can either alternate sides or do one side at a time.

Instruction.1: Start with a straight bar or ez bar attachment set to the bottom of the machine. Squat the weight up into a standing position and walk a few steps back
Instruction.2: Push your butt back to initiate the movement and then push your butt forward until you're back in a standing position.
Instruction.3: To protect yourself from injury, always maintain a flat back on any exercise.

Instruction.1: Start with a straight bar or easy bar attachment. Squat the weight up into a standing position and walk a few steps back.
Instruction.2:
Push your butt back to initiate the movement while lifting one of your legs.
Then push your butt forward until you're back in a standing position.
Instruction.3: Compete your given amount of reps, then switch to opposite leg.
Instruction.4: To protect yourself from injury, always maintain a flat back.

Instruction.1: This exercise works best with a rope attachment but can be done with anything. The attachment should be set to the bottom of the machine.
Instruction.2:
Face away from the cable machine, straddle the cable itself, and grab the attachment.
Walk a few steps away.
Instruction.3: Break at the hips while maintaining a flat back and mostly extended knees.
Instruction.4: Push hips forward until you are back in a standing position.

WorkoutName: Cable Standing Straight Leg Glute Kickback

Instruction.1: Start with a straight bar attachment set to the bottom of the machine. Squat the weight up into a standing position and walk a few steps back.
Instruction.2: Stand with a staggered stance. Push your butt back to initiate the movement and then push your butt forward until you're back in a standing position.
Instruction.3: To protect yourself from injury, always maintain a flat back on any exercise.

Instruction.1: Use an ankle attachment. Bring a bench over to the cables. The cable should be set to hip height.
Instruction.2: Push your ankle straight back, extending at the hip. Hold for a one count when you feel a contraction in your glutes.
Instruction.3: Then flex at the hips until you are back into your original position.

Instruction.1: Start with handles set to the bottom of the machine. Grab a box, stand on top of the box, squat the weight up into a standing position.
Instruction.2: Push your butt back to initiate the movement and then push your butt forward until you're back in a standing position.
Instruction.3: To protect yourself from injury, always maintain a flat back on any exercise.

WorkoutName: Cable Incline Bench Straight Leg Kickback

Instruction.1: Use an ankle attachment. Bring a bench over to the cables. Put the bench at incline level. The cable should be set to shoulder height.
Instruction.2: Push your ankle straight back, extending at the hip. Hold for a one count when you feel a contraction in your glutes.
Instruction.3: Then flex at the hips until you are back into your original position.

Instruction.1: Start with a straight bar or easy bar attachment .
Instruction.2: Place the bar in your elbows, squat straight up and then walk back a few steps.
Instruction.3: Break at your knees and hips to initiate the squat. Make sure you maintain a flat back.
Instruction.4: Squat all the way back to a standing position.

Instruction.1: Use an ankle attachment. The cable should be set halfway up the crossover machine.
Instruction.2: Start with a bent knee position. Push your ankle straight back, extending at the hip. Hold for a one count when you feel a contraction in your glutes.
Instruction.3: Then flex at the hips until you are back into your original position.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing with your feet about hip-width apart and holding the bar in the crook of your elbows, with your palms facing towards your body.
Instruction.2: Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, bend at the hips and lower your torso forward until it is nearly parallel to the ground.
Instruction.3: Push through your heels to extend your hips and raise your body back to the starting position.

WorkoutName: Cable Standing Straight Leg Mid Kickback

Instruction.1: Use an ankle attachment. The cable should be set to halfway up the crossover machine.
Instruction.2: Push your ankle straight back, extending at the hip. Hold for a one count when you feel a contraction in your glutes.
Instruction.3: Then flex at the hips until you are back into your original position.

WorkoutName: Cable Single Arm Rear Delt Row

Instruction.1: Use a handle attachment, grab with an overhand grip and take a position with the cable crossing your body.
Instruction.2: Pull your elbows back while flaring your elbows outward.

Instruction.1: Hold the TRX straps and lean away from the anchor point until the straps are taut.
Instruction.2: Keep both elbows mostly extended and raise both arms out and upwards.
Instruction.3: You should make a Y shape with your arms during the back portion of the exercise.

Instruction.1: Grab the TRX straps and lean away from the anchor point until the strap is taut.
Instruction.2: Start with an overhand grip. Pull your elbows back and rotate your grip.
Instruction.3: By the time your elbows reach your side, your palms should be facing upwards.

Instruction.1: Hold the TRX strap with one hand.
Instruction.2: Lean back until the strap is taut. Fully extend your elbow.
Instruction.3: Pull your elbow behind the body. Make sure to avoid twisting. Try to keep your shoulders even.

Instruction.1: Grasp the TRX handles with both hands, keeping your arms extended and your shoulders away from your ears.
Instruction.2: Keep your abs engaged, roll forward onto your toes, and extend your arms in front of you.
Instruction.3: Slowly lower your body down to the ground, keeping your arms straight and your abs engaged.
Instruction.4: When your head gets between your arms, pause for a moment and then use your abs to pull your body back up to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Begin in a kneeling position with the TRX straps adjusted to mid-calf length.
Instruction.2: Grasp the TRX handles with both hands, keeping your arms extended and your shoulders away from your ears.
Instruction.3: Keep your abs engaged, roll forward onto your toes, and extend your arms in front of you.
Instruction.4: Slowly lower your body down to the ground, keeping your arms straight and your abs engaged.

Instruction.1: Stand facing away from the TRX straps and grab the handles with both hands.
Instruction.2: Step forward so that your body is in a plank position, with your arms straight and your body in a straight line from your head to your heels.
Instruction.3: Keeping your arms straight, slowly lift your arms out to the side, keeping them at the same height as your shoulders. Your body should form a "T" shape.

Instruction.1: Stand facing away from the TRX straps and grab the handles with both hands.
Instruction.2: Step away so your body is leaning away from the anchor point.
Instruction.3: Flex your elbows and pull your elbows straight back behind your body.
Instruction.4: Make sure to keep your elbows flared outward.

Instruction.1: Hold the TRX straps and lean away from the anchor point.
Instruction.2: Pull your elbows back while externally rotating your shoulder joint. Your arms should make a W shape at the back portion of the exercise.

WorkoutName: Seated Upper Trap And Suprispinatus Stretch

Instruction.1: Sit on the back of your palm.
Instruction.2: Straighten the back and pull the shoulders back.
Instruction.3: Lean your head to the opposite side.

Instruction.1: Place a tube roller or half tube on the ground parallel to your body.
Instruction.2: Lie on the tube making sure your whole back and neck are supported.
Instruction.3: Knees bent and on the ground, lower back flat on the tube and chin tucked in.
Instruction.4: Bring your arms by you hips and pull shoulders back.
Instruction.5: This is your starting position. Raise arms and drop them back towards the ground over your head

Instruction.1: Place a foam roller on the floor perpendicular to your body.
Instruction.2: Sit and lie back onto it aiming for your mid back to be in contact with the roller.
Instruction.3: Gently tilt your hips backward, squeeze glutes and engage core to protect the lower back.
Instruction.4: Support head on palms, elbows rotated in. Slightly lift hips off the ground.

WorkoutName: Lat And Shoulder External Rotation Stretch 1 Kneeling Dowel
Lat And Shoulder External Rotation Stretch 2 Kneeling Dowel

Instruction.1: Kneel in front of a bench, placing your elbows on with palms facing up while holding the dowel at shoulder width.
Instruction.2: Sit your hips back onto your heels, pressing the head in between the arms.
Instruction.3: You should feel a stretch in your lats, triceps and deep in the shoulder joint.
Instruction.4: You can add movement (bend-extended arms) to mobilise the shoulder joint.

WorkoutName: Lat And Shoulder External Rotation Stretch 3 Kneeling Dowel

Instruction.1: Kneel in front of a bench, placing your elbows on with palms facing up while holding the dowel at shoulder width.
Instruction.2: Sit your hips back onto your heels, pressing the head in between the arms.
Instruction.3: You should feel a stretch in your lats, triceps and deep in the shoulder joint.
Instruction.4: You can add movement (bend-extended arms) to mobilise the shoulder joint.

Instruction.1: Sit on your heels and reach out your arms on the floor while pressing the chest towards the ground.
Lie on a bench holding a dumbbell over your shoulder, straight arm.
Instruction.2: Slowly lower your arm towards the ground (overhead position).
Instruction.3: Pause in the stretched position.
Instruction.4: Bend your elbow to return to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Lay on your front placing your palms under your shoulders
Instruction.2: Keep the elbows bent and close to your body
Instruction.3: Lift your upper body off the ground supporting your weight on your forearms
Instruction.4: Keep the hips on the ground

Instruction.1: Lay on your front placing your palms under your shoulders
Instruction.2: Keep the elbows bent and close to your body
Instruction.3: Lift your upper body off the ground supporting your weight on your palms
Instruction.4: Keep the hips on the ground

Instruction.1: Stand up straight with a good form.
Instruction.2: Send your hips back and start tilting the upper body.
Instruction.3: Maintain a straight back as you aim for your toes.
Instruction.4: Your range depends on your hamstring flexibility.

Instruction.1: Lie on your front leaning your forehead on the back of your palms.
Instruction.2: Squeeze your glutes and tilt your hips backwards (flattens the front of your hips against the ground).
Instruction.3: Raise your chest off the ground and lower it without resting on the ground before the next rep

Instruction.1: Lie on your front and bring your arms into the "W" position.
Instruction.2: Squeeze your glutes and tilt your hips backwards (flattens the front of your hips against the ground).
Instruction.3: Raise your chest off the ground and lower it without resting on the ground before the next rep.

Instruction.1: Lie on your front and bring your arms in the "I" position, thumbs pointing the ceiling.
Instruction.2: Squeeze your glutes and tilt your hips backwards (flattens the front of your hips against the ground).
Instruction.3: Raise your chest off the ground and lower it without resting on the ground before the next rep.

WorkoutName: Lumbar Extensor Mobilisation Supine Bent Knees Peanut Tool

Instruction.1: Lie on your back with your feet on a bench. Place a peanut tool under your lower back.
Instruction.2: Adjust pressure by pressing your heels into the bench. Roll back and forth or side to side
Instruction.3: Maintain a neutral lower back (do not tilt the pelvis).

Instruction.1: Lie on the floor keeping your knees bent and the feet on the floor.
Instruction.2: Place a massage ball under your lower back and move around till the ball presses into a tight/sore spot.
Instruction.3: If you use a foam roller you would have to be seated and leaning back into the roller.

Instruction.1: Lie on your front with your arms by your side, palms facing down.
Instruction.2: Tense your back muscles to raise both ends of your body off the ground.
Instruction.3: Keep your core engaged as you will be supporting your weight on your belly.

Instruction.1: Stand up straight with a good form.
Instruction.2: Send your hips back and start tilting the upper body.
Instruction.3: Maintain a straight back as you aim for your toes.
Instruction.4: Lower the bar to the floor by bending your knees and keeping your back straight.

Instruction.1: Stand tall, hinge at hips, and reach hands to the floor.
Instruction.2: Walk hands forward into a plank position.
Instruction.3: Walk feet towards hands and repeat the motion.

Instruction.1: Lie on your front, arms outstretched to the side.
Instruction.2: Raise head and chest off the ground.
Instruction.3: Raise and lower your arms (flapping wings motion) by contracting and relaxing the muscles in between your shoulder blades.

Instruction.1: From the standing or seated position straighten your back.
Instruction.2: Pull the shoulders back but keep them relaxed.
Instruction.3: Move shoulders backwards and return to the starting, relaxed position.

Instruction.1: From the standing or seated position straighten your back.
Instruction.2: Pull the shoulders back but keep them relaxed.
Instruction.3: Move shoulders towards from your ears and return to the starting, relaxed position.

Instruction.1: While seated on a bench, place your palms on the bench by your sides
Instruction.2: Palm placement should allow room for the fingers to grip the edge of the bench
Instruction.3: Try to lift your bodyweight off the bench by pushing the palms into the bench
Instruction.4: Lockout your elbows and repeat or hold isometrically

Instruction.1: While seated on a bench, place your palms on the bench by your sides
Instruction.2: Palm placement should allow room for the fingers to grip the edge of the bench
Instruction.3: Try to lift your bodyweight off the bench by pushing the palms into the bench
Instruction.4: Lockout your elbows and hold isometrically

Instruction.1: From the standing or seated position straighten your back.
Instruction.2: Pull the shoulders back but keep them relaxed.
Instruction.3: Move shoulders away from your ears and return to the starting, relaxed position.

Instruction.1: Use a bench or an object like a chair to elevate your feet.
Instruction.2: Slowly lower your body (scapula) while keeping your elbows locked (this is key)
Instruction.3: Slowly raise your body back to the start position.

Instruction.1: Use a bench or an object to elevate your feet.
Instruction.2: Lower your head towards the floor by bending your elbows
Instruction.3: Push through your hands and return to the starting pike position.
Instruction.4: Repeat

Instruction.1: Start in a plank position. Push your hips up toward the ceiling.
Instruction.2: Lower your head towards the floor by bending your elbows
Instruction.3: Push through your hands and return to the starting pike position.
Instruction.4: Repeat

Instruction.1: Start in a plank position and raise your hips toward the ceiling.
Instruction.2: Slowly lower your body (scapula) while keeping your elbows locked (this is key)
Instruction.3: Slowly raise your body back to the start position.

Instruction.1: Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, arms and shoulders fully extended.
Instruction.2: Pull your body up until your chin is above the bar.
Instruction.3: Lower your body back to starting position.

Instruction.1: Lay underneath a fixed horizontal bar and grab the bar with a wide overhand grip.
Instruction.2: Pull your body straight up to the bar.
Instruction.3: Return to the starting position, your arms fully extended. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Grab the bar shoulder width apart with a supinated grip (palms facing you)
Instruction.2: With your body hanging and arms fully extended, pull yourself up until your chin is past the bar.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to starting position. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Grasp the chin-up bar with an underhand grip, shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Place your feet on the ground, legs bent slightly.
Instruction.3: Use your legs to assist as you pull your chin above the bar.

Instruction.1: Grasp the chin-up bar with an underhand grip, shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Place your feet on the ground, legs bent slightly.
Instruction.3: Use your legs to assist as you pull your chest to the bar.

Instruction.1: Grasp the chin-up bar with a mixed grip, shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Place your feet on the ground, legs bent slightly.
Instruction.3: Use your legs to assist as you pull your chin above the bar.

Instruction.1: Grasp the chin-up bar with an overhand grip, shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Place your feet on the ground, legs bent slightly.
Instruction.3: Use your legs to assist as you pull your chin above the bar.

Instruction.1: Lay underneath a fixed horizontal bar and grab the bar with a wide overhand grip.
Instruction.2: Pull your body straight up to the bar.
Instruction.3: Return to the starting position, your arms fully extended. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Grab a door frame or a rack and place your feet near the frame.
Instruction.2: Start with your elbows extended, row your body towards your hands.
Instruction.3: Return to the starting position, your arms fully extended. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Lay underneath a fixed horizontal bar and grab the bar with an underhand grip.
Instruction.2: Pull your body straight up to the bar.
Instruction.3: Return to the starting position, your arms fully extended. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Set up rings at a high point.
Instruction.2: Grip rings and lean back, arms extended.
Instruction.3: Pull chest to rings, keeping body straight.

Instruction.1: Grab the bar shoulder width apart with a supinated grip (palms facing you)
Instruction.2: With your body in an "L" position and arms fully extended, pull yourself up until your chin is past the bar.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to starting position. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, arms and shoulders fully extended. Pull your legs up until you're in an "L" position.
Instruction.2: Pull your body up until your chin is above the bar.
Instruction.3: Lower your body back to starting position.

Instruction.1: Grab the bar shoulder width apart with a supinated grip (palms facing you)
Instruction.2: With your body hanging and arms fully extended, pull yourself up and lean backwards. Try to touch your chest to the bar.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to starting position. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Grab the rings shoulder width apart with a supinated grip (palms facing you)
Instruction.2: With your body hanging and arms fully extended, pull yourself up until your chin is past the rings.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to starting position. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Grasp the rings with an overhand grip, arms and shoulders fully extended.
Instruction.2: Pull your body up until your chin is above the rings.
Instruction.3: Lower your body back to starting position.

Instruction.1: Grab the rings shoulder width apart with a pronated grip (palms facing away).
Instruction.2: With your body hanging and arms fully extended, pull yourself up and rotate your fists until your chin is past the rings.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to starting position. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Lie face down on the floor with your arms fully extended in front of you.
Instruction.2: Simultaneously raise your arms, legs and chest off of the floor and hold the position.
Instruction.3: Slowly lower your arms, legs and chest back to the starting position. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet a little past shoulder width apart with a slight bend at your knee. Place your hands behind the back of your head.
Instruction.2: Keeping your back straight, rotate your hips to bring your shoulders down towards the floor. Stop when your chest is parallel with the floor.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent and raise one leg.
Instruction.2: Without changing the bend in your knee, bend at your hips, and lower your torso until it's almost parallel to the floor.
Instruction.3: Tense your glutes and then bring yourself back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Set up a bar at mid way up your quad. Place the working leg against the bar.
Instruction.2: Place one foot behind. You should only be on your toes on that back foot. Your front foot should be planted flat the entire time.
Instruction.3: Bend your back knee and push your hips back. Look for a stretch in your front hamstring.
Instruction.4: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward again until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Place a barbell at about midway up your thigh. Press your quads into the barbell.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back while leaving your knees mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Lie face-down on a stability ball, hips centered, feet anchored, hands behind your head.
Instruction.2: Engage your core, lift your upper body until aligned with legs, keeping your neck neutral.
Instruction.3: Lower your torso slowly back to the starting position, maintaining control and steady breathing.

Instruction.1: Lie face down on a stability ball, hands on the floor, legs extended straight.
Instruction.2: Engage glutes and lower back, raising legs until aligned with your torso.
Instruction.3: Slowly lower legs back down without touching the ground, maintaining core engagement. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Place one knee on a bench.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back while leaving your knee mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Standing up straight with feet shoulder width apart.
Instruction.2: Holding the kettlebell in both hands in front of your pelvis, engage your shoulder blades, as if you are trying to touch them together.
Instruction.3: Release the shrug and repeat

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell with both hands in front of your thighs.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees, keeping your back straight.
Instruction.3: Lift the kettlebell upwards towards your chest and lower - repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell with both hands in front of your thighs.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees, keeping your back straight.
Instruction.3: Holding the kettlebell in both hands engage your shoulder blades, as if you are trying to touch them together. Release the shrug.

Instruction.1: Leaning across the back section of the bench, with feet firmly on the floor and with arms hanging to the sides.
Instruction.2: Holding the kettlebell in both hands engage your shoulder blades, as if you are trying to touch them together. Release the shrug.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, hold one kettlebell in each hand at your sides.
Instruction.2: Lift your shoulders upward while keeping arms straight.
Instruction.3: Lower shoulders back down, repeat for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Start with a kettlebell between your legs, hinge at hips, swing it upward.
Instruction.2: Lift kettlebell to chest level, elbows high, engaging shoulders.
Instruction.3: Lower kettlebell back down, maintaining control. Repeat for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell with both hands in front of your thighs.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees, keeping your back straight.
Instruction.3: Lift the kettlebell upwards towards your chest and lower - repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell with both hands in front of your thighs.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees, keeping your back straight.
Instruction.3: Lift the kettlebell upwards towards your chest and lower - repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell with both hands in front of your thighs.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees, keeping your back straight.
Instruction.3: Lift the kettlebell upwards towards your chest and lower - repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder width apart bending forward at the hips as far as comfortable. Place off-hand on the same side thigh for stability.
Instruction.2: Hold the kettlebell in one hand, straight armed and pointing towards the floor.
Instruction.3: Keeping your arm straight, swing the kettlebell behind you as far as comfortable.
Instruction.4: Return to the starting position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder width apart, shifting one foot behind you. Hold the kettlebell in the same hand as the leg shifted backwards.
Instruction.2: Bend forwards at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knee, keeping your back straight.
Instruction.3: Lift the kettlebell upwards towards your chest and lower - repeat.
