Instruction.1: Rest your upper back on the bench and place soles of your feet firmly on the floor keeping torso and thighs suspended and parallel to the floor.
Instruction.2: Hold the kettlebell with both hands above your chest, keeping your arms straight.
Instruction.3: Keeping your arms straight, move the kettlebell in the direction of your head until your arms are parallel to the floor.
Instruction.4: Return to starting to position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, kettlebell in one hand.
Instruction.2: Bend at hips, row kettlebell to chest.
Instruction.3: Alternate hands for each row.

Instruction.1: Stand with kettlebell between legs.
Instruction.2: Hinge at hips, grab kettlebell, pull to chest and rotate at the torso

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, hold a kettlebell in each hand.
Instruction.2: Hinge at hips, keep back straight, and pull both kettlebells to hips.

WorkoutName: Kettlebell Single Arm Row On Bench

Instruction.1: Start by standing in front of a flat bench with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a kettlebell in one hand.
Instruction.2: Place your other hand on the bench for support, and bend at the waist so that your chest is parallel to the ground.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, row the kettlebell up towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blade together as you do so.
Instruction.4: Make sure to keep your elbow close to your body and your core engaged throughout the movement.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell with both hands in front of your thighs.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees, keeping your back straight.
Instruction.3: Return to standing position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet slightly wider than shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell between your legs, with your knees slightly bent.
Instruction.2: Keeping your back straight, swing the kettlebell upwards until the kettlebell is level with your chest and carefully lower.
Instruction.3: Repeat

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder width apart, shifting one foot behind you. Hold the kettlebell in both hands in front of your thighs.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees and keep your back straight.
Instruction.3: Return to the upright position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell with both hands in front of your chest.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at the hips keeping your back and knees straight and the kettlebell close to your chest.
Instruction.3: Return to standing position and thrust your pelvis forward.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, kettlebell between legs.
Instruction.2: Hinge at hips, swing kettlebell between legs.
Instruction.3: Swing kettlebell up, switch hands at the top, and repeat in a fluid motion.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Bend at hips and knees to lift kettlebells.
Instruction.3: Stand tall, then lower.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, kettlebells outside legs
Instruction.2: Hinge at hips, swing kettlebells forward, then back.
Instruction.3: Thrust hips to swing kettlebells upward, keeping arms straight.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, kettlebell between legs.
Instruction.2: Hinge at hips, grip kettlebell, and swing it overhead.
Instruction.3: Extend hips and knees, lock out arms at the top.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, holding kettlebells in front.
Instruction.2: Hinge at hips, keeping back straight, and lower kettlebells towards ground.
Instruction.3: Return to start position, squeezing glutes at the top.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, kettlebell between legs, grip with one hand, hinge at hips.
Instruction.2: Swing kettlebell forcefully forward, using hip thrust, arm straight.
Instruction.3: Swing kettlebell back between legs, repeat for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Begin with feet hip-width apart, one foot forward, kettlebell between feet.
Instruction.2: Hinge at hips, grip kettlebell, and stand tall.
Instruction.3: Lower kettlebell with control, then repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet wide apart, toes pointing slightly outward, and kettlebell on the floor between your feet.
Instruction.2: Bend at hips and knees, keeping back straight, and grip the kettlebell handle.
Instruction.3: Lift the kettlebell by extending hips and knees, stand up straight, and return to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Begin by lying face down on the floor with a kettlebell in each hand, arms extended.
Instruction.2: Lift your chest and legs off the ground simultaneously while squeezing your glutes and raising the kettlebells.
Instruction.3: Lower your body and kettlebells back to the floor, then repeat for the desired number of reps.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, kettlebell in one hand, arm fully extended, and hinge at hips.
Instruction.2: Lift opposite leg straight behind you, forming a straight line from head to heel.
Instruction.3: Hold for 15-30 seconds, switch sides, and repeat for a balanced kettlebell superman hold.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder width apart, lifting one foot off the floor behind you. Hold the kettlebell in the same arm as the lifted leg.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you extend your lifted leg behind you, keeping your back straight - holding out your arm to the side for balance.
Instruction.3: Return to the upright position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing with your feet hip-width apart and holding a kettlebell at one side of your body, with your palms facing your thighs.
Instruction.2: Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, bend at the hips and knees to lower the kettlebell down towards the ground.
Instruction.3: As the kettlebell reaches the ground, use your legs and glutes to push through your heels and extend your hips and knees to raise your body back to the starting position.
Instruction.4: Repeat the movement for the desired number of reps, then switch sides and repeat the exercise with the kettlebell on the opposite side of your body.

Instruction.1: Stand in front of a box or bench with your feet shoulder-width apart with a kettlebell in a goblet position.
Instruction.2: Lower your body into a squat position, sitting back onto the box and pausing for a moment before standing back up.
Instruction.3: Push through your heels to return to the standing position.

Instruction.1: Set up a bar at mid way up your quad. Place the working leg against the bar.
Instruction.2: Place one foot behind. You should only be on your toes on that back foot. Your front foot should be planted flat the entire time.
Instruction.3: Bend your back knee and push your hips back. Look for a stretch in your front hamstring.
Instruction.4: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward again until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Place a barbell at about midway up your thigh. Press your quads into the barbell.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back while leaving your knees mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you're back in a standing position.

WorkoutName: Kettlebell Half Kneeling Goblet Romanian Deadlift

Instruction.1: Place one knee on a bench and hold a kettlebell in a goblet position.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back while leaving your knee mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Place one knee on a bench and hold a kettlebell.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back while leaving your knee mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, kettlebell in each hand, hinge at hips.
Instruction.2: Pull kettlebells while flaring your elbows, squeezing shoulder blades. Keep back flat.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, hold one kettlebell in each hand at your sides, and lean forward.
Instruction.2: Lift your shoulders backward while keeping arms straight.
Instruction.3: Lower shoulders back down, repeat for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Place the band under your feet. Stand upright.
Instruction.2: Elevate your shoulder blades and then depress back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Anchor the band at shoulder height. Take a few steps away until the band is taut.
Instruction.2: Retract your shoulder blades straight back in schools. Then protract to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Loop the band under one of your feet. The other end of the bed should be in your hand between your thumb and pointer finger.
Instruction.2: Press the band straight up towards the ceiling. Until your elbow is fully extended.

Instruction.1: Stand with one or both feet on one end of a band. Take a double overhand roughly shoulder width grip.
Instruction.2: Pull your elbows straight up the ceiling. Aim to get the band to chin level or slightly higher.

Instruction.1: Place the band at about eye level. Fall into a kneeling position.
Instruction.2: The knee that is on the ground should be the same side as the working arm. Stick your chest out.
Instruction.3: And then pull your elbow straight back. Flex your lats and then extend into the starting position.

Instruction.1: Place the band just above our level. Take a few steps away until the band is taut.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back slightly. Extend and flex at the shoulder joint.

Instruction.1: Stand on your band with both feet.
Instruction.2: Hinge forward at the hips while keeping a flat back.
Instruction.3: Let your arms hang freely, then pull your elbows straight back toward the ceiling.

Instruction.1: Anchor the band to a stable point.
Instruction.2: Take a half squat position and hold there.
Instruction.3: Perform a row while holding the squat position.

WorkoutName: Band Squat Hold Single Arm Row

Instruction.1: Anchor the band to a stable point and take a half squat position.
Instruction.2: Hold the band loop in one hand and pull your elbow straight back.

Instruction.1: Anchor band to a stable point.
Instruction.2: Step back until there is no slack in the band and hold the end of the band with one hand.
Instruction.3: Pull through the elbow straight back.

Instruction.1: Anchor the band to a high point. Go into a seated position.
Instruction.2: Grab the loop of the band and pull your upper arm to your side.

Instruction.1: Anchor the band at hip level. Take a few steps away until the band is taut.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back while keeping your back flat until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings.

Instruction.1: Anchor the band to the lowest point possible. Straddle the band and then grab with both hands.
Instruction.2: Take a few steps away until the band is taut.
Instruction.3: Push your butt back until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings. Then extend the hips back into the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand on your band with both feet.
Instruction.2: Hinge forward at the hips while keeping a flat back.
Instruction.3: Hinge until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.4: Push your hips back forward until you are in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Grab the band with a shoulder width grip. Point your arms straight in front of you.
Instruction.2: Retract your shoulder blades and shoulder joint until the band taps your chest.

Instruction.1: Start with a band anchored to a high point. Stagger your stance.
Instruction.2: Pull the band to the bridge of your nose.

Instruction.1: Start by standing between the two anchored bands with your feet shoulder-width apart and the bands positioned at a high point.
Instruction.2: Grasp the ends of each band with your hands, keeping your palms facing each other.
Instruction.3: Keeping your arms slightly bent and your back straight, slowly pull the bands away from your body until your arms are extended straight out to the sides. Hold for a second, then slowly release back to the starting position. Repeat for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Sit cross-legged on the floor and bring your arms out to the sides at shoulder height.
Instruction.2: Cross your right arm over your left, bending both elbows so that your forearms are parallel to the floor.
Instruction.3: Lift your elbows towards the ceiling and bring your hands together, then drop your chin towards your chest.
Instruction.4: Hold for a few breaths, then release your arms and repeat on the other side.

Instruction.1: Begin by sitting cross-legged on the floor.
Instruction.2: Slowly drop your chin towards your chest, feeling a stretch in the back of your neck.
Instruction.3: Inhale and lift your head up, then exhale and drop your right ear towards your right shoulder.
Instruction.4: Hold for a few breaths, then switch sides and repeat the stretch.

Instruction.1: Sit cross-legged on the floor and interlace your fingers behind your head.
Instruction.2: Drop your chin to your chest and roll your head to the right, bringing your right ear towards your right shoulder.
Instruction.3: Slowly roll your head back to center, then over to the left so that your left ear is close to your left shoulder.
Instruction.4: Repeat the movement from side to side, keeping your shoulders relaxed and breathing deeply.

WorkoutName: Thread The Needle Hip Over Knees

Instruction.1: Start on your hands and knees in a tabletop position.
Instruction.2: Slide your right knee up between your hands and place your right foot close to your left wrist.
Instruction.3: Take your left leg back and lower it down to the ground, keeping your toes tucked.
Instruction.4: Twist your torso to the right and reach your right arm underneath your left arm, threading the needle. Hold for a few breaths, then switch sides.

Instruction.1: Begin in a tabletop position with your hands and knees on the ground.
Instruction.2: Sit back onto your heels and extend your arms out in front of you.
Instruction.3: Rest your forehead on the ground.
Instruction.4: Hold for a few breaths and then release.

WorkoutName: Child Pose Arms Extended Left Right

Instruction.1: Begin in a tabletop position with your hands and knees on the ground.
Instruction.2: Sit back onto your heels and extend your arms out in front of you to one side.
Instruction.3: Rest your forehead on the ground.
Instruction.4: Hold for a few breaths and then repeat on the other side.

Instruction.1: Begin in a tabletop position with your hands and knees on the ground.
Instruction.2: Sit back onto your heels and place your arms at your sides with your palms facing up.
Instruction.3: Rest your forehead on the ground.
Instruction.4: Hold for a few breaths and then release.

Instruction.1: Begin in a lunge position with your right foot forward and your left foot back.
Instruction.2: Place your right hand on a block or the ground on the outside of your right foot.
Instruction.3: Reach your left arm overhead and then round your spine, bringing your left hand to your right ear.
Instruction.4: Look down towards your right foot as you reach your left arm towards the front of the room, feeling a stretch in your side body. Hold for a few breaths and then switch sides.

WorkoutName: Extended side Angle Pose With Block

Instruction.1: Begin in a lunge position with your right foot forward and your left foot back.
Instruction.2: Place a block on the outside of your right foot and place your right hand on top of it.
Instruction.3: Look down towards your right foot as you reach your left arm towards the front of the room, feeling a stretch in your side body. Hold for a few breaths and then switch sides.

WorkoutName: Gate Pose Rounding Spine Looking Up

Instruction.1: Begin in a kneeling position with your knees hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Extend your right leg out to the side, placing your foot flat on the ground.
Instruction.3: Reach your right arm overhead and then round your spine, bringing your right hand to your left ear.
Instruction.4: Look down towards your left foot as you reach your left arm towards your right foot, feeling a stretch in your side body. Hold for a few breaths and then switch sides.

Instruction.1: Begin in a comfortable seated position on your mat, with your legs crossed and your spine straight.
Instruction.2: Extend your right arm up toward the ceiling and bend it at the elbow, bringing your right hand behind your head.
Instruction.3: Reach your left arm behind your back and bend it at the elbow, bringing your left hand up between your shoulder blades.
Instruction.4: Clasp your hands behind your back, trying to touch your fingertips together. If you can't quite reach, you can use a strap or towel to bridge the gap between your hands.

Instruction.1: Lie down on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor.
Instruction.2: Lift your feet off the floor and bring your knees towards your chest.
Instruction.3: Reach inside your knees and hold onto the outside edges of your feet.
Instruction.4: Gently pull your knees towards your armpits and rock side to side for a few breaths.

Instruction.1: Start by lying down on your stomach on a yoga mat or a comfortable surface.
Instruction.2: Place your elbows underneath your shoulders, keeping your forearms parallel to each other.
Instruction.3: Press your palms and forearms firmly into the ground to lift your chest up, while keeping your hips and legs relaxed.
